delete comment meta "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
===================================================================

NAME
----

delete comment meta - Remove metadata matching criteria from a comment. You can match based on

SYNOPSIS
--------

Remove metadata matching criteria from a comment. You can match based on
the key, or key and value. Removing based on key and value will keep
from removing duplicate metadata with the same key. It also allows
removing all metadata matching key, if needed.

`delete_comment_meta()` allows you to delete any meta values stored
against comments, which have been set using
[add\_comment\_meta()](/Function_Reference/add_comment_meta "Function Reference/add comment meta").
Similar method to
[delete\_post\_meta()](/Function_Reference/delete_post_meta "Function Reference/delete post meta").

USAGE
-----

` <?php   delete_comment_meta( $comment_id, $meta_key, $meta_value );?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$comment_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Comment ID
    Default: *None*

 `$meta_key` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Metadata key
    Default: *None*

 `$meta_value` 
:   ([*mixed*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Mixed "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Metadata value
    Default: *None*

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(boolean)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   False for failure. True for success.

